+      <tr><td><span class="taboo-pair"><span class="from">disease</span>, <span class="from">illness</span>, <span class="from">disorder</span>, <span class="from">pathology</span>, <span class="from">medical condition</span></span></td><td>A packed cluster: bodily or learned mechanisms, impaired control, need for treatment, eligibility for care, reduced contempt, possible accommodation, and a different style of accountability.</td></tr>
+      <tr><td><span class="taboo-pair"><span class="from">real</span>, <span class="from">really</span>, <span class="from">true</span>, <span class="from">actually</span>, <span class="from">is</span></span></td><td>A request for privileged category membership after the observable facts are already fixed. Replace it with: what would we expect to observe, and what response would change?</td></tr>
+      <tr><td><span class="taboo-pair"><span class="from">just</span>, <span class="from">merely</span>, <span class="from">only</span></span></td><td>An attempt to collapse a multi-cause pattern into one small description, usually either "bad choice" or "body problem," while discarding the rest.</td></tr>
+      <tr><td><span class="taboo-pair"><span class="from">choice</span>, <span class="from">voluntary</span></span></td><td>Actions that can respond to reasons, incentives, planning, threat, promise, habit, environment, and available help. This comes in degrees and contexts, not one switch.</td></tr>
+      <tr><td><span class="taboo-pair"><span class="from">responsible</span>, <span class="from">blameworthy</span>, <span class="from">moral failing</span></span></td><td>Questions about which responses help: trust or distrust, help or refusal, treatment or punishment, compassion or anger, repair demands or exclusion.</td></tr>
