+      <tr><td><span class="taboo-pair"><span class="from">choice</span>, <span class="from">voluntary</span></span></td><td>Actions that can respond to reasons, incentives, planning, threat, promise, habit, environment, and available help. This comes in degrees and contexts, not one switch.</td></tr>
+      <tr><td><span class="taboo-pair"><span class="from">responsible</span>, <span class="from">blameworthy</span>, <span class="from">moral failing</span></span></td><td>Questions about which responses help: trust or distrust, help or refusal, treatment or punishment, compassion or anger, repair demands or exclusion.</td></tr>
+    </tbody></table>
+    <p>Taboo rewrite: Does the person show a recurring harmful drinking pattern; what mechanisms keep it going; how much does it respond to ordinary reasons and changed circumstances; which interventions reduce harm; and which forms of accountability produce better outcomes?</p>
+    <p>The irreplaceable word has been located. If the intended question means "should this pattern receive the social status attached to the medical label?", the taboo rewrite stalls because the label itself is the prize being contested. That is not an extra fact hiding inside the drinker; it is a fight over how to sort compassion, payment, coercion, blame, and help.</p>
